[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Teleports heavy resources (timber, stone, marble, ore) straight from the ground to the nearest stockpile that has space. No more dragging them back one-at-a-time after chopping down a forest.[/size]

[size=3][b]Core behaviour[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Teleport to nearest stockpile[/b] — when a heavy resource drops (from chopping, mining, etc.), it's routed to the nearest stockpile that can accept it. Stockpiles are picked by available space, not just proximity.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Dump-site fallback[/b] — when every stockpile for a resource is full, the item goes to your designated dump site for that resource type (timber, stone/marble, ore — each has its own independent dump). Dump sites are filled in a grid from top-left to bottom-right. If no dump site is set, the item drops on the ground where it was.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Immersive Mode[/b] (default on) — each teleport costs 3 energy. Disable immersive mode to make teleports free if you'd rather not worry about energy.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Setting dump sites[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3]Stand where you want the dump site to be, then press the appropriate set-location key (defaults: 7 for timber, 8 for ore, 9 for stone/marble).[/size]
[*][size=3]All keybinds are rebindable in the config. Controller bindings aren't currently exposed — use keyboard keys.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Master toggle[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Default toggle key: 6[/b] (rebindable). Flips auto-teleport on and off mid-play without opening the config menu.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Performance Smoothness[/b] — slider that throttles how aggressively the mod scans for eligible drops. Lower values are lighter on CPU; higher values catch drops faster. Default is a sensible middle ground.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Other[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Main menu update notice[/b] — flags when a newer version of this mod (or other mods in my collection) is on Nexus. Click to open the mod's page. Opt-out via "Check for Updates".[/size]
[/list]

